# Migration Assistant TUI (Go module)
#
# The TUI module has its own migrationAssistantTUI/.gitignore that
# covers /bin/, /dist/, coverage.{out,html}, *.test, *.prof. The root
# rules below catch only the cases where artifacts can escape the
# module boundary:
#
#   - `go build ./cmd/tui` from the repo ROOT (not from inside the
#     module) lands the binary at /tui. Guard against that.
#   - A misdirected `go build -o migrationAssistantTUI/tui …` lands
#     a binary at the module root, outside its own /bin/ rule.
#
# We deliberately do NOT add `migrationAssistantTUI/**/*.test` etc.
# here — the module-local .gitignore already owns those.
/tui
migrationAssistantTUI/tui
migrationAssistantTUI/cmd/tui/tui
# Go workspace files — these are user-local, never committed.
go.work
go.work.sum

